@startuml
!include <C4/C4_Context>
!include <C4/C4_Container>

/'
C2 – Container Diagram

Purpose:
Shows the high-level technical building blocks (*Containers) that make up
the Software System, their responsibilities, and how they communicate
with each other, with *People, and with *External Software Systems.

*People:
- Human users of the system, defined at the System Context (C1) level

*Software System:
- Software System: The system under consideration

*Containers:
- Container: A separately deployable and/or runnable unit that executes
  code or stores data (e.g., web UI, API, background worker, database)

*External Software Systems:
- Other Software Systems that interact with one or more containers

*Relationships:
- People -> Containers: Use the system via client or interface containers
- Container -> Container: Communicate using synchronous or asynchronous mechanisms
- Container -> External Software System: Integrate via APIs, messaging, or data exchange

Architecture Notes:
- This diagram captures the system’s high-level architecture
  (e.g., client–server, n-tier, microservices, event-driven)
- Containers should represent runtime and deployment boundaries
- Communication styles and protocols should be shown when architecturally significant
- Internal design patterns (e.g., MVC, layered, hexagonal) are out of scope
  and belong to the Component (C3) level
- Infrastructure and deployment topology are typically documented separately
'/

Person(user, "User", "A person who browses and reads recipes.")
System_Boundary(recipe_blog_boundary, "RecipeBlog") {
    Container(web_app, "Web App", "Single-Page Application", "Provides the user interface.")
    Container(api_service, "API Service", "REST API", "Handles recipe logic and data.")
    ContainerDb(database, "Database", "Relational Database", "Stores recipe text and metadata.")
}
System_Ext(cdn, "CDN", "Stores and delivers high-resolution recipe images.")

Rel(user, web_app, "Uses", "HTTPS")
Rel(web_app, api_service, "Makes API calls to", "JSON/HTTPS")
Rel(api_service, database, "Reads from and writes to")
Rel(api_service, cdn, "Uploads images to")
Rel(web_app, cdn, "Fetches images from")

@enduml

